  "description": "On 30 May and 2 June, I encountered relatively large numbers of ibis at Lower Latham and Beebe Draw. Some odd-balls, I chose to photograph rather than write-up a description. I can say that on this bird, the face pattern seemed to show lines like a Glossy (not in color, but the presence of pale lines on the skin) plus a very limited amount of pale feathering. The bird seemed intermediate in coloring. So, I photographed it.Behaviors: feeding in wet grassCall: none heardPlumage: adult Alternate",
